    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p>What may be the reason behind this Wrong Output ?</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Your assumptions about the date format string are wrong, the output is <em>correct</em>.</p>\n\n<pre><code>y   Year\nY   Week year\nD   Day in year\nd   Day in month\nM   Month in year\nm   Minute in hour\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/text/SimpleDateFormat.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/text/SimpleDateFormat.html</a></p>\n\n<p><code>Y</code> Week year will usually give incorrect results around new year. <code>D</code> will give incorrect results from February. So your format appeared fine most of last month.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1927754,
      "reputation" : 6137,
      "user_id" : 1737819,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 89,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fb16bd6e98bf74bb8324af88c35d503d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Developer Marius Žilėnas",
