  "title" : "java.util.Date is generating a wrong date?",
  "body" : "<p>Here's my code:</p>\n\n<pre><code>java.util.Date TODAY = new java.util.Date();     \nSimpleDateFormat SDF = new SimpleDateFormat( \"YYYY-MM-DD\" );\nSystem.out.println ( SDF.format( TODAY ) );'\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And the result is:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>2015-02-33</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>But today's date is 2015-02-02!</p>\n\n<p>What may be the reason behind this wrong output?</p>\n"
